[1] Cholera - Cuba (Artemis Province)
Date: Fri 14 Sep 2012
Source: Marti Noticias [edited]
http://www.martinoticias.com/content/article/14772.html


A Cuban of about 65 years of age died of cholera in the village of Bahia Honda, along with 16 other people who were sent to the Institute of Tropical Medicine Pedro Kour√≠ (IPK) in Havana, apparently after eating lobsters at a family feast, lobsters contaminated with the cholera bacillus. This was reported to Marti Noticias by independent journalist Moses Leonardo Rodriguez from a town adjacent to Bahia Honda in the province of Artemis.

Local health authorities are focusing on direct contact with the population the same precautionary measures taken during the recent outbreak of cholera in Manzanillo, but without mentioning the disease by its name.

The cases in Bahia Honda do not seem to be related to the outbreak in Manzanillo.
[Byline: Rolando Cartaya]

