[2] Cholera - Dominican Republic (Santiago Province)
Date: Fri 14 Sep 2012
Source: Noticias SIN [machine transl.] [edited]
http://www.noticiassin.com/2012/09/mas-de-80-personas-presentan-sintomas-similares-al-colera-en-sector-de-santiago/


More than 80 people have symptoms similar to cholera in the area known as Los Arroyos de Palo Quemados in Santiago. Inhabitants of the area indicated to SIN News, that the people affected all had significant diarrhea. The alarm is active with the death of a 90-year-old, who died last Sunday. Before the situation the authorities of the Ministry of Public Health came to the area to hear the reports.

Residents say the outbreak has arisen due to the fact that some people consume rain water for drinking and to do the housework.

